cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.MA 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with the performance analysis of a wireless sensor node powered by RF energy harvesting, which involves the transmission and reception of information. The proposed cooperative beam selection scheme also involves optimizing the transmission of data while satisfying the energy harvesting requirement. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper focuses on wireless sensor networks and proposes a scheme to enhance the energy harvesting performance of a sensor node. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a cooperative beam selection scheme to optimize the energy harvesting performance of a wireless sensor node, which can be seen as a control problem. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with the transmission and reception of RF signals, which can be considered as a form of multimedia communication. 
5. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems): The proposed cooperative beam selection scheme involves multiple agents (i.e., the multiuser MIMO system) working together to optimize the energy harvesting performance of the sensor node.
